page.title: 09Stodmarsh Reserve/Wild life
page.content: Many different{birds}can be seen at the reserve, some{migratory birds spend the winter there and some only stop to feed and rest. There are many {insects}there so the birds find food easily. You can find{slugs}and{snails everywhere. In the lakes you can see {fish}and{eels. There are{trees}on the reserve, mainly{alder}but also there are {willow, ash}and{oak. Wild flowers cover lots of the land and they attract different kinds of {butterflies. In the winter 84/85 wardens reported that there were{three {bitterns. }The bad weather caused the lakes to freeze for about a month. The River Stour was still running but the {bitterns}were too shy to go and feed there; one died of starvation.
